The Q-Function
𝐐̂t=𝐂t+𝐀tT𝐕t+1𝐀t=[QtcostStTStRt]+[AtTBtT]𝐕t+1[AtBt]=[QtcostStTStRt]+[AtT𝐕t+1AtAtT𝐕t+1BtBtT𝐕t+1AtBtT𝐕t+1Bt]=[Qtcost+AtT𝐕t+1AtStT+AtT𝐕t+1BtSt+BtT𝐕t+1AtRt+BtT𝐕t+1Bt]=[𝐐̂𝐱𝐱𝐐̂𝐱𝐮𝐐̂𝐮𝐱𝐐̂𝐮𝐮]𝐪̂t=[qtrt]+[AtT𝐕t+1𝐚tBtT𝐕t+1𝐚t]+[AtT𝐯t+1BtT𝐯t+1]=[𝐪̂𝐱𝐪̂𝐮]
\begin{aligned}
\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_t  &= \mathbf{C}_t + \mathbf{A}_{t}^T \mathbf{V}_{t+1} \mathbf{A}_{t}\\
&= \begin{bmatrix} Q_t^{cost} & S_t^{\!T}  \\ S_t& R_t \end{bmatrix} + \begin{bmatrix}  A_t^{\!T}  \\ B_t^{\!T}\end{bmatrix} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} \begin{bmatrix}  A_t  & B_t\end{bmatrix}\\
&= \begin{bmatrix} Q_t^{cost} & S_t^{\!T}  \\ S_t& R_t \end{bmatrix} + \begin{bmatrix}  A_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} A_t &  A_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} B_t\\ B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} A_t &  B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} B_t\end{bmatrix} \\
&=  \begin{bmatrix} Q_t^{cost} + A_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} A_t & S_t^{\!T} + A_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} B_t\\ S_t + B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} A_t & R_t+  B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} B_t\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{x}} & \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{u}} \\ \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{x}} & \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}} \end{bmatrix}\\
\qquad \hat{\mathbf{q}}_t &= \begin{bmatrix}  q_t  \\ r_t\end{bmatrix} + \begin{bmatrix}  A_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} \mathbf{a}_t \\ B_t^{\!T}\mathbf{V}_{t+1} \mathbf{a}_t\end{bmatrix}  +  \begin{bmatrix}  A_t^{\!T} \mathbf{v}_{t+1}  \\ B_t^{\!T}\mathbf{v}_{t+1} \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} \hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{x}} \\ \hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{u}} \end{bmatrix}
\end{aligned}

Optimal Control at Each Step
Minimize 𝐐t\mathbf{Q}_t over 𝐮t\mathbf{u}_t. Partition the Q-function matrix:
𝐐̂t=[𝐐̂𝐱𝐱𝐐̂𝐱𝐮𝐐̂𝐮𝐱𝐐̂𝐮𝐮],𝐪̂t=[𝐪̂𝐱𝐪̂𝐮]\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_t = \begin{bmatrix} \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{x}} & \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{u}} \\ \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{x}} & \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}} \end{bmatrix}, \qquad \hat{\mathbf{q}}_t = \begin{bmatrix} \hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{x}} \\ \hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{u}} \end{bmatrix}
Setting ∇𝐮t𝐐t=0\nabla_{\mathbf{u}_t} \mathbf{Q}_t = 0:
𝐮t*=𝐊t𝐱t+𝐤t\boxed{\mathbf{u}_t^* = \mathbf{K}_t \mathbf{x}_t + \mathbf{k}_t}
𝐊t=−𝐐̂𝐮𝐮−1𝐐̂𝐮𝐱=−(Rt+BtT𝐕t+1Bt)−1(St+BtT𝐕t+1At)𝐤t=−𝐐̂𝐮𝐮−1𝐪̂𝐮=(Rt+BtT𝐕t+1Bt)−1(rt+BtT𝐕t+1𝐚t+BtT𝐯t+1)
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{K}_t &= -\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}}^{-1}\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{x}} = -\left( R_t+  B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} B_t  \right)^{-1}  ( S_t + B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} A_t )\\
\mathbf{k}_t &= -\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}}^{-1}\hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{u}} = \left( R_t+  B_t^{\!T} \mathbf{V}_{t+1} B_t \right)^{-1}  (r_t + B_t^{\!T}\mathbf{V}_{t+1} \mathbf{a}_t+ B_t^{\!T}\mathbf{v}_{t+1})
\end{aligned}




The optimal policy is affine in state: 𝐮t*=𝐊t𝐱t+𝐤t\mathbf{u}_t^* = \mathbf{K}_t \mathbf{x}_t + \mathbf{k}_t. When 𝐜t=0\mathbf{c}_t = 0 and 𝐚t=0\mathbf{a}_t = 0, then 𝐤t=0\mathbf{k}_t = 0 (linear policy).

Value Function Update
Substituting 𝐮t*\mathbf{u}_t^* back into 𝐐t\mathbf{Q}_t gives the value function:
Vt*(𝐱t)=12𝐱tT𝐕t𝐱t+𝐱tT𝐯t+constV_t^*(\mathbf{x}_t) = \frac{1}{2}\mathbf{x}_t^T \mathbf{V}_t \mathbf{x}_t + \mathbf{x}_t^T \mathbf{v}_t + \mathrm{const}
where
𝐕t=𝐐̂𝐱𝐱+𝐐̂𝐱𝐮𝐊t=𝐐̂𝐱𝐱−𝐐̂𝐱𝐮𝐐̂𝐮𝐮−1𝐐̂𝐮𝐱\mathbf{V}_t = \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{x}} + \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{u}}\mathbf{K}_t = \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{x}} - \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{u}} \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}}^{-1}\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{x}}
𝐯t=𝐪̂𝐱+𝐐̂𝐱𝐮𝐤t=𝐪̂𝐱−𝐐̂𝐱𝐮𝐐̂𝐮𝐮−1𝐪̂𝐮\mathbf{v}_t = \hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{x}} + \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{u}}\mathbf{k}_t  = \hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{x}} - \hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{x}\mathbf{u}}\hat{\mathbf{Q}}_{\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}}^{-1}\hat{\mathbf{q}}_{\mathbf{u}}
The cost-to-go at time tt is again quadratic (in 𝐱t\mathbf{x}_t) — so the structure repeats at t−1,t−2,…,0t-1, t-2, \dots, 0.

